<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="264" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1863,2035]" pageId="13" pageNumber="264">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1863,1888]" pageId="13" pageNumber="264">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Postcranium with upper postocular third shiny with no pruinescence. Wing hyaline, slightly brown infuscation at pterostigma and apex of cell r 
<subScript attach="left" box="[676,700,1914,1928]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="264">2+3</subScript>
. Tergite 8 subrectangular, with posterior margin desclerotized. Epandrium with posterodorsal lobe much longer than anterodorsal lobe, sickle-shaped. Anterior cercus, when viewed laterally, with mesial branch forming a small L-shaped cercal bridge. Posterior cercus sickle-shaped, upwardly directed, placed parallel to posterior lobe of epandrium.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
