<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="266" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,151,1802]" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,151,176]" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">Description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[352,456,151,176]" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">Holotype</typeStatus>
<specimenCount box="[464,485,152,175]" pageId="15" pageNumber="266" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
(
<figureCitation box="[501,606,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1828,1850]" captionTargetBox="[213,1372,194,1798]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[213,1373,193,1807]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Macrostomus falcatus sp. nov. A–B, holotype ♂, C–L paratype ♂ from La Paz, Zongo. A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Sternite 8, ventral view; E. Tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; F. Epandrium, detached, lateral view (longer setae broken); G. Terminalia (epandrium, hypandrium and phallus removed), lateral view; H. Terminalia, posterior view; I. Cercal bridge of anterior cercus (outlined) and ventral projection of cercus, anterior view; J. Anterior cercus, dorsal view (cercal bridge outlined); K. Hypandrium, ejaculatory apodeme and phallus, lateral view; L. Hypandrium, posterior view (alveoli highlighted); M. Holotype labels. Scale bars, figure A = 1 mm; B–L = 0.2 mm. Abbreviation: crbd, cercal bridge; vpc, ventral projection of cercus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594955/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
). Body length 3.0 mm; wing length 3.0 mm. Head dichoptic. Frons shiny brown, slightly wider than width of anterior ocellus. One pair of proclinate ocellar setae. Face narrower than frons, slightly wider ventrally. Postcranium shiny brown, sparsely gray pruinose, except upper postocular third shiny without pruinescence. Inner vertical seta stouter than outer vertical seta, latter subequal in length to uniseriate postocular row of setae; 2 pairs of dorsal occipital setae. Gena with 2 small setae and postgena with 1–2 minute setae. Antenna velvety black with postpedicel short setulose. Proboscis mainly shiny yellow. Palpus brown to black. Thorax shiny brown to black, more distinctly brown pruinose on disc of scutum, scutellum and mediotergite. Postpronotal lobe slightly yellow. Thoracic chaetotaxy: 3 antepronotals small; 1 postpronotal stout, 1 weak; 4 dorsocentrals; 1 presutural supra-alar; 0 postsutural supra-alar; 1 postalar; 2 minute proepisternals; 2 notopleurals, posterior stouter; 2 pairs of scutellars, outer pair weaker; 4 laterotergitals. Legs shiny yellow with distal 1/5 of hind femur, entire hind tibia and tarsus light brown to black. Legs longer setae: hind femur with 1 anteroventral seta at base of distal fourth; hind tibia with 4 slender dorsal setae; hind tarsomere 1 with 1 median slender dorsal seta. Wing (
<figureCitation box="[227,329,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1828,1850]" captionTargetBox="[213,1372,194,1798]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[213,1373,193,1807]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Macrostomus falcatus sp. nov. A–B, holotype ♂, C–L paratype ♂ from La Paz, Zongo. A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Sternite 8, ventral view; E. Tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; F. Epandrium, detached, lateral view (longer setae broken); G. Terminalia (epandrium, hypandrium and phallus removed), lateral view; H. Terminalia, posterior view; I. Cercal bridge of anterior cercus (outlined) and ventral projection of cercus, anterior view; J. Anterior cercus, dorsal view (cercal bridge outlined); K. Hypandrium, ejaculatory apodeme and phallus, lateral view; L. Hypandrium, posterior view (alveoli highlighted); M. Holotype labels. Scale bars, figure A = 1 mm; B–L = 0.2 mm. Abbreviation: crbd, cercal bridge; vpc, ventral projection of cercus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594955/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
) hyaline, slightly brown infuscate at pterostigma and apex of cell r 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1078,1102,598,612]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">2+3</subScript>
. Veins M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1210,1218,598,612]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">1</subScript>
, M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1257,1265,598,612]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">2</subScript>
and CuA+CuP entirely evanescent. Last section of vein M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[629,637,637,651]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">4</subScript>
longer than dm-m. Cell dm short and slightly projected. Halter whitish. Abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[277,416,661,686]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1828,1850]" captionTargetBox="[213,1372,194,1798]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[213,1373,193,1807]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Macrostomus falcatus sp. nov. A–B, holotype ♂, C–L paratype ♂ from La Paz, Zongo. A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Sternite 8, ventral view; E. Tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; F. Epandrium, detached, lateral view (longer setae broken); G. Terminalia (epandrium, hypandrium and phallus removed), lateral view; H. Terminalia, posterior view; I. Cercal bridge of anterior cercus (outlined) and ventral projection of cercus, anterior view; J. Anterior cercus, dorsal view (cercal bridge outlined); K. Hypandrium, ejaculatory apodeme and phallus, lateral view; L. Hypandrium, posterior view (alveoli highlighted); M. Holotype labels. Scale bars, figure A = 1 mm; B–L = 0.2 mm. Abbreviation: crbd, cercal bridge; vpc, ventral projection of cercus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594955/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">Figs 10A, B</figureCitation>
) shiny brown (specimen from alcohol). Tergites 1–3 with slightly longer setae posteriorly. 
<typeStatus box="[151,249,698,722]" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">Paratype</typeStatus>
<specimenCount box="[259,283,698,721]" pageId="15" pageNumber="266" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
: Tergite 8 (
<figureCitation box="[419,522,697,722]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1828,1850]" captionTargetBox="[213,1372,194,1798]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[213,1373,193,1807]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Macrostomus falcatus sp. nov. A–B, holotype ♂, C–L paratype ♂ from La Paz, Zongo. A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Sternite 8, ventral view; E. Tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; F. Epandrium, detached, lateral view (longer setae broken); G. Terminalia (epandrium, hypandrium and phallus removed), lateral view; H. Terminalia, posterior view; I. Cercal bridge of anterior cercus (outlined) and ventral projection of cercus, anterior view; J. Anterior cercus, dorsal view (cercal bridge outlined); K. Hypandrium, ejaculatory apodeme and phallus, lateral view; L. Hypandrium, posterior view (alveoli highlighted); M. Holotype labels. Scale bars, figure A = 1 mm; B–L = 0.2 mm. Abbreviation: crbd, cercal bridge; vpc, ventral projection of cercus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594955/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">Fig. 10C</figureCitation>
) subrectangular, with posterior margin desclerotized, without distal sinus; base with shallow sinus. Sternite 8 (
<figureCitation box="[503,606,733,758]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1828,1850]" captionTargetBox="[213,1372,194,1798]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[213,1373,193,1807]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Macrostomus falcatus sp. nov. A–B, holotype ♂, C–L paratype ♂ from La Paz, Zongo. A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Sternite 8, ventral view; E. Tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; F. Epandrium, detached, lateral view (longer setae broken); G. Terminalia (epandrium, hypandrium and phallus removed), lateral view; H. Terminalia, posterior view; I. Cercal bridge of anterior cercus (outlined) and ventral projection of cercus, anterior view; J. Anterior cercus, dorsal view (cercal bridge outlined); K. Hypandrium, ejaculatory apodeme and phallus, lateral view; L. Hypandrium, posterior view (alveoli highlighted); M. Holotype labels. Scale bars, figure A = 1 mm; B–L = 0.2 mm. Abbreviation: crbd, cercal bridge; vpc, ventral projection of cercus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594955/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">Fig. 10D</figureCitation>
) without posterolateral saddle-shaped projection. Tergite 8 and sternite 8 (
<figureCitation box="[159,258,769,794]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1828,1850]" captionTargetBox="[213,1372,194,1798]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[213,1373,193,1807]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Macrostomus falcatus sp. nov. A–B, holotype ♂, C–L paratype ♂ from La Paz, Zongo. A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Sternite 8, ventral view; E. Tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; F. Epandrium, detached, lateral view (longer setae broken); G. Terminalia (epandrium, hypandrium and phallus removed), lateral view; H. Terminalia, posterior view; I. Cercal bridge of anterior cercus (outlined) and ventral projection of cercus, anterior view; J. Anterior cercus, dorsal view (cercal bridge outlined); K. Hypandrium, ejaculatory apodeme and phallus, lateral view; L. Hypandrium, posterior view (alveoli highlighted); M. Holotype labels. Scale bars, figure A = 1 mm; B–L = 0.2 mm. Abbreviation: crbd, cercal bridge; vpc, ventral projection of cercus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594955/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">Fig. 10E</figureCitation>
) narrowly articulated. Epandrium (
<figureCitation box="[652,749,769,794]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1828,1850]" captionTargetBox="[213,1372,194,1798]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[213,1373,193,1807]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Macrostomus falcatus sp. nov. A–B, holotype ♂, C–L paratype ♂ from La Paz, Zongo. A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Sternite 8, ventral view; E. Tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; F. Epandrium, detached, lateral view (longer setae broken); G. Terminalia (epandrium, hypandrium and phallus removed), lateral view; H. Terminalia, posterior view; I. Cercal bridge of anterior cercus (outlined) and ventral projection of cercus, anterior view; J. Anterior cercus, dorsal view (cercal bridge outlined); K. Hypandrium, ejaculatory apodeme and phallus, lateral view; L. Hypandrium, posterior view (alveoli highlighted); M. Holotype labels. Scale bars, figure A = 1 mm; B–L = 0.2 mm. Abbreviation: crbd, cercal bridge; vpc, ventral projection of cercus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594955/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">Fig. 10F</figureCitation>
) with posterodorsal lobe much longer than anterodorsal lobe, with small mid projection anteriorly; without anterodorsal cleft and anteroventral cleft as inconspicuous unsclerotized area; with longer setae posteriorly (setae broken in figure). Anterior cercus (
<figureCitation box="[1168,1306,841,866]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1828,1850]" captionTargetBox="[213,1372,194,1798]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[213,1373,193,1807]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Macrostomus falcatus sp. nov. A–B, holotype ♂, C–L paratype ♂ from La Paz, Zongo. A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Sternite 8, ventral view; E. Tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; F. Epandrium, detached, lateral view (longer setae broken); G. Terminalia (epandrium, hypandrium and phallus removed), lateral view; H. Terminalia, posterior view; I. Cercal bridge of anterior cercus (outlined) and ventral projection of cercus, anterior view; J. Anterior cercus, dorsal view (cercal bridge outlined); K. Hypandrium, ejaculatory apodeme and phallus, lateral view; L. Hypandrium, posterior view (alveoli highlighted); M. Holotype labels. Scale bars, figure A = 1 mm; B–L = 0.2 mm. Abbreviation: crbd, cercal bridge; vpc, ventral projection of cercus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594955/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">Figs 10G, H</figureCitation>
) somewhat small, well sclerotized, with mesial setae; mesial branch (
<figureCitation box="[814,918,877,902]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1828,1850]" captionTargetBox="[213,1372,194,1798]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[213,1373,193,1807]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Macrostomus falcatus sp. nov. A–B, holotype ♂, C–L paratype ♂ from La Paz, Zongo. A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Sternite 8, ventral view; E. Tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; F. Epandrium, detached, lateral view (longer setae broken); G. Terminalia (epandrium, hypandrium and phallus removed), lateral view; H. Terminalia, posterior view; I. Cercal bridge of anterior cercus (outlined) and ventral projection of cercus, anterior view; J. Anterior cercus, dorsal view (cercal bridge outlined); K. Hypandrium, ejaculatory apodeme and phallus, lateral view; L. Hypandrium, posterior view (alveoli highlighted); M. Holotype labels. Scale bars, figure A = 1 mm; B–L = 0.2 mm. Abbreviation: crbd, cercal bridge; vpc, ventral projection of cercus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594955/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">Fig. 10H</figureCitation>
) forming small L-shaped cercal bridge when viewed laterally; mesial connection of cercal bridge rounded (
<figureCitation box="[848,940,913,938]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1828,1850]" captionTargetBox="[213,1372,194,1798]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[213,1373,193,1807]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Macrostomus falcatus sp. nov. A–B, holotype ♂, C–L paratype ♂ from La Paz, Zongo. A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Sternite 8, ventral view; E. Tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; F. Epandrium, detached, lateral view (longer setae broken); G. Terminalia (epandrium, hypandrium and phallus removed), lateral view; H. Terminalia, posterior view; I. Cercal bridge of anterior cercus (outlined) and ventral projection of cercus, anterior view; J. Anterior cercus, dorsal view (cercal bridge outlined); K. Hypandrium, ejaculatory apodeme and phallus, lateral view; L. Hypandrium, posterior view (alveoli highlighted); M. Holotype labels. Scale bars, figure A = 1 mm; B–L = 0.2 mm. Abbreviation: crbd, cercal bridge; vpc, ventral projection of cercus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594955/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">
Fig. 
<date box="[900,940,914,938]" pageId="15" pageNumber="266" value="2010-01">10I</date>
</figureCitation>
, outlined) when viewed posteriorly. Median cercus (
<figureCitation box="[238,340,949,974]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1828,1850]" captionTargetBox="[213,1372,194,1798]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[213,1373,193,1807]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Macrostomus falcatus sp. nov. A–B, holotype ♂, C–L paratype ♂ from La Paz, Zongo. A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Sternite 8, ventral view; E. Tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; F. Epandrium, detached, lateral view (longer setae broken); G. Terminalia (epandrium, hypandrium and phallus removed), lateral view; H. Terminalia, posterior view; I. Cercal bridge of anterior cercus (outlined) and ventral projection of cercus, anterior view; J. Anterior cercus, dorsal view (cercal bridge outlined); K. Hypandrium, ejaculatory apodeme and phallus, lateral view; L. Hypandrium, posterior view (alveoli highlighted); M. Holotype labels. Scale bars, figure A = 1 mm; B–L = 0.2 mm. Abbreviation: crbd, cercal bridge; vpc, ventral projection of cercus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594955/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">Fig. 10H</figureCitation>
) semi globose, upwardly directed with longer setae anterodorsally. Posterior cercus (
<figureCitation box="[1291,1428,949,974]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1828,1850]" captionTargetBox="[213,1372,194,1798]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[213,1373,193,1807]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Macrostomus falcatus sp. nov. A–B, holotype ♂, C–L paratype ♂ from La Paz, Zongo. A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Sternite 8, ventral view; E. Tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; F. Epandrium, detached, lateral view (longer setae broken); G. Terminalia (epandrium, hypandrium and phallus removed), lateral view; H. Terminalia, posterior view; I. Cercal bridge of anterior cercus (outlined) and ventral projection of cercus, anterior view; J. Anterior cercus, dorsal view (cercal bridge outlined); K. Hypandrium, ejaculatory apodeme and phallus, lateral view; L. Hypandrium, posterior view (alveoli highlighted); M. Holotype labels. Scale bars, figure A = 1 mm; B–L = 0.2 mm. Abbreviation: crbd, cercal bridge; vpc, ventral projection of cercus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594955/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">Figs 10G, H</figureCitation>
) wider basally, upwardly directed, simple, acuminate distally, placed in parallel to posterior lobe of epandrium. Ventral projection of cercus (
<figureCitation box="[474,564,1021,1046]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1828,1850]" captionTargetBox="[213,1372,194,1798]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[213,1373,193,1807]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Macrostomus falcatus sp. nov. A–B, holotype ♂, C–L paratype ♂ from La Paz, Zongo. A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Sternite 8, ventral view; E. Tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; F. Epandrium, detached, lateral view (longer setae broken); G. Terminalia (epandrium, hypandrium and phallus removed), lateral view; H. Terminalia, posterior view; I. Cercal bridge of anterior cercus (outlined) and ventral projection of cercus, anterior view; J. Anterior cercus, dorsal view (cercal bridge outlined); K. Hypandrium, ejaculatory apodeme and phallus, lateral view; L. Hypandrium, posterior view (alveoli highlighted); M. Holotype labels. Scale bars, figure A = 1 mm; B–L = 0.2 mm. Abbreviation: crbd, cercal bridge; vpc, ventral projection of cercus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594955/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">
Fig. 
<date box="[525,564,1022,1046]" pageId="15" pageNumber="266" value="2010-01">10I</date>
</figureCitation>
) flat, fused medially, bilobate dorsally, with inconspicuous ventral lobe with 2 small setae. Dorsal hypoproctal lobe (
<figureCitation box="[601,699,1057,1082]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1828,1850]" captionTargetBox="[213,1372,194,1798]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[213,1373,193,1807]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Macrostomus falcatus sp. nov. A–B, holotype ♂, C–L paratype ♂ from La Paz, Zongo. A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Sternite 8, ventral view; E. Tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; F. Epandrium, detached, lateral view (longer setae broken); G. Terminalia (epandrium, hypandrium and phallus removed), lateral view; H. Terminalia, posterior view; I. Cercal bridge of anterior cercus (outlined) and ventral projection of cercus, anterior view; J. Anterior cercus, dorsal view (cercal bridge outlined); K. Hypandrium, ejaculatory apodeme and phallus, lateral view; L. Hypandrium, posterior view (alveoli highlighted); M. Holotype labels. Scale bars, figure A = 1 mm; B–L = 0.2 mm. Abbreviation: crbd, cercal bridge; vpc, ventral projection of cercus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594955/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">Fig. 10J</figureCitation>
) bigger than ventral lobe of hypoproct, both distinctly setose. Hypandrium (
<figureCitation box="[307,445,1093,1118]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1828,1850]" captionTargetBox="[213,1372,194,1798]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[213,1373,193,1807]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Macrostomus falcatus sp. nov. A–B, holotype ♂, C–L paratype ♂ from La Paz, Zongo. A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Sternite 8, ventral view; E. Tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; F. Epandrium, detached, lateral view (longer setae broken); G. Terminalia (epandrium, hypandrium and phallus removed), lateral view; H. Terminalia, posterior view; I. Cercal bridge of anterior cercus (outlined) and ventral projection of cercus, anterior view; J. Anterior cercus, dorsal view (cercal bridge outlined); K. Hypandrium, ejaculatory apodeme and phallus, lateral view; L. Hypandrium, posterior view (alveoli highlighted); M. Holotype labels. Scale bars, figure A = 1 mm; B–L = 0.2 mm. Abbreviation: crbd, cercal bridge; vpc, ventral projection of cercus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594955/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">Figs 10K, L</figureCitation>
) slightly wider distally, bifid and membranous distally. Ejaculatory apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[1326,1428,1093,1118]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1828,1850]" captionTargetBox="[213,1372,194,1798]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[213,1373,193,1807]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Macrostomus falcatus sp. nov. A–B, holotype ♂, C–L paratype ♂ from La Paz, Zongo. A. Habitus, lateral view; B. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; C. Tergite 8, dorsal view; D. Sternite 8, ventral view; E. Tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; F. Epandrium, detached, lateral view (longer setae broken); G. Terminalia (epandrium, hypandrium and phallus removed), lateral view; H. Terminalia, posterior view; I. Cercal bridge of anterior cercus (outlined) and ventral projection of cercus, anterior view; J. Anterior cercus, dorsal view (cercal bridge outlined); K. Hypandrium, ejaculatory apodeme and phallus, lateral view; L. Hypandrium, posterior view (alveoli highlighted); M. Holotype labels. Scale bars, figure A = 1 mm; B–L = 0.2 mm. Abbreviation: crbd, cercal bridge; vpc, ventral projection of cercus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594955/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">Fig. 10K</figureCitation>
) with dorsal lamella very short. Phallus slightly longer than hypandrium.
</paragraph>
