<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="266" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,151,1802]" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1417,1442]" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the Latin 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rafael &amp; Marques" authorityYear="2019" box="[538,626,1417,1441]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="266" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falcatus">
<emphasis box="[538,626,1417,1441]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">falcatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
= sickle-shaped, which refers to the shape of the posterior lobe of epandrium and the posterior cercus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1417,1489,1514]" pageId="15" pageNumber="266" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,151,1802]" box="[199,1417,1489,1514]" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,313,1489,1514]" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">Variation.</emphasis>
Specimen from alcohol distinctly paler (brown) than specimen without alcohol preservation (black).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="266" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,151,1802]" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1525,1550]" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Rafael &amp; Marques, 2019" authorityName="Rafael &amp; Marques" authorityYear="2019" box="[323,571,1525,1549]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="266" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falcatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[323,571,1525,1549]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">Macrostomus falcatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[579,670,1525,1550]" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[579,670,1525,1550]" pageId="15" pageNumber="266" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
appears closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" box="[973,1387,1525,1550]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="266" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albicaudatus">
<emphasis box="[973,1156,1525,1549]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">M. albicaudatus</emphasis>
Rafael &amp; Cumming
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" box="[151,572,1561,1586]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="266" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trombetensis">
<emphasis box="[151,333,1561,1585]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">M. trombetensis</emphasis>
Rafael &amp; Cumming
</taxonomicName>
based on a similar epandrium with the posterodorsal lobe longer than the anterodorsal lobe and posterior cercus elongate, upwardly directed and somewhat simple. It differs from both species by the posterior cercus without protuberances (versus with protuberances or setae), apex of hypandrium with an apical projection somewhat membranous, bifid when viewed posteriorly (versus absent). In the key presented by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rafael, J. A. &amp; Cumming, J. M." box="[310,629,1705,1730]" pageId="15" pageNumber="266" pagination="109 - 121" refId="ref14883" refString="Rafael, J. A. &amp; Cumming, J. M. (2015) Revision of the genus Macrostomus Wiedemann (Diptera, Empididae, Empidinae). IV. The amazonensis species-group. Zootaxa, 3947, 109 - 121. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3947.1.7" type="journal article" year="2015">Rafael &amp; Cumming (2015)</bibRefCitation>
, this species runs to couplet 5 separating 
<taxonomicName authority="Rafael &amp; Cumming" authorityName="Rafael &amp; Cumming" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="266" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amazonensis">
<emphasis box="[1132,1317,1706,1729]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="266">M. amazonensis</emphasis>
Rafael &amp; Cumming
</taxonomicName>
from 
